cff-version: 1.2.0
message: If you use this work, please cite it using the metadata below.
type: dataset
title: QUIC Implementation Performance Evaluation Across Multiple Server and Client
  Configurations
abstract: This dataset documents an experiment evaluating the performance of several
  QUIC implementations under varying network conditions. The methodology involved
  configuring and running both server and client software with different values for
  bandwidth limits, file sizes, and QUIC implementation types across two nodes.  Performance
  was assessed through measurements of elapsed time and energy consumption during
  data transfers, along with verification of downloaded files via checksums. Evaluation
  scripts aggregated results from multiple runs to generate performance reports and
  visualizations.
